bead /biːd/

(beads) 

1. N-COUNT Beads are small pieces of coloured glass, wood, or plastic with a hole through the middle. Beads are often put together on a piece of string or wire to make jewellery. 中间有孔的小珠子 

例： ...a string of beads. …一串珠子。 

2. N-COUNT A bead of liquid or moisture is a small drop of it. (液体或湿气的) 小滴 

例： ...beads of blood. …滴滴鲜血。

